column2: Please indicate whether or not you consent to participate
column3: How many years of software development experience do you have?
column7: Do you have editing experience in Stack Overflow posts?
column8: How many posts did you edit using Stack Overflow editing system?
column9: How many of them were rejected?
column16: How confident are you to edit posts using Stack Overflow editing system?

column17: I was not sure whether my edits are good or bad, so my confident was low. Even I cannot understand much from the reviewers comment why my edits actually rejected. The reasons were too general.
I learn from the rejected edit. If I can have guidelines from Stack Overflow before submitting edits, my condent would high.
Because when I start I try to edit the grammatical mistake, adding Greeting & Gratitude and so on. Generally there have some problems in most of the post. So I fell confident when I edit.
I could not understand why my edits were rejected.

SO editing system rejects insignificant edits (e.g. minimum character change requirement, rule-out unimportant addition such as salutation/ Hi All, hello, etc.) even before submitting the edit. So, I think it does a good job.
My edits are rejected even after I followed the editing guidelines. Unfortunately, I did not understand the causes of rejection clearly.
